.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "August 2025" "Version 1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.br
.B echo "command" | hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Simple Shell
is a basic UNIX command line interpreter that executes commands read from standard input. It implements a subset of the functionality of 
.BR sh (1).

.B Simple Shell
can operate in both interactive and non-interactive modes. In interactive mode, it displays a prompt and waits for user input. In non-interactive mode, it reads commands from standard input.

.SH USAGE
After compilation, the shell can be invoked by:
.br
.B ./hsh

.SH FEATURES
.TP
.B Interactive Mode
Displays a prompt (#cisfun$) and waits for user commands
.TP
.B Non-interactive Mode  
Reads commands from standard input (pipes, redirections)
.TP
.B PATH Support
Automatically searches for executables in PATH environment variable
.TP
.B Built-in Commands
Supports exit and env built-in commands
.TP
.B Error Handling
Displays appropriate error messages for invalid commands

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell
.TP
.B env
Print the current environment variables

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Interactive mode:
.nf
$ ./hsh
#cisfun$ ls
file1 file2 file3
#cisfun$ /bin/pwd
/home/user
#cisfun$ exit
$
.fi

.TP
Non-interactive mode:
.nf
$ echo "ls" | ./hsh
file1 file2 file3
$ echo "/bin/pwd" | ./hsh
/home/user
.fi

.SH RETURN VALUE
.B Simple Shell
returns the exit status of the last command executed. If a command is not found, it returns 127. For built-in commands, it returns 0 on success.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PATH
Used to search for executable files

.SH FILES
.TP
.B hsh
The executable shell program

.SH ERRORS
When an error occurs, 
.B simple_shell
prints an error message to standard error with the format:
.br
./hsh: line_number: command: not found

.SH LIMITATIONS
.B Simple Shell
does not support:
.br
- Pipes (|)
.br  
- Redirections (>, <, >>)
.br
- Background processes (&)
.br
- Variable expansions ($VAR)
.br
- Quotes for arguments with spaces
.br
- Command substitution
.br
- Wildcards (* ?)

.SH AUTHORS
See AUTHORS file for list of contributors.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR bash (1),
.BR execve (2),
.BR fork (2),
.BR wait (2)

.SH BUGS
No known bugs. Report bugs to the project repository.

